<a name="api"></a>
<section class="section--center mdl-grid mdl-grid--no-spacing mdl-shadow--2dp">
  <div class="mdl-card mdl-cell mdl-cell--12-col-desktop mdl-cell--6-col-tablet mdl-cell--4-col-phone">
    <div class="mdl-card__supporting-text">
      <h4>Simple API</h4>
      We really belive that it should stay simple. Yep, that simple. We can fake it and make it look more complex just to charge more, but we know better. <a href="//docs.scanr.xyz">Full documentation</a>.
      <div class="mdl-tabs mdl-js-tabs mdl-js-ripple-effect">
        <div class="mdl-tabs__tab-bar">
            <a href="#curl" class="mdl-tabs__tab is-active">curl</a>
            <a href="#node" class="mdl-tabs__tab">Node.js</a>
            <a href="#ruby" class="mdl-tabs__tab">Ruby</a>
        </div>

        <div class="mdl-tabs__panel is-active" id="curl">
          <h5>request</h5>
          <code>curl -F "image=@/path/to/image.png" http://api.scanr.xyz/ocr?token=YOUR_TOKEN</code><br/>
          <h5>response</h5>
<pre><code>HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
{text: 'Hello world!'}</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="mdl-tabs__panel" id="node">
          <h5>request</h5>
<pre><code>npm install scanr
var scanr = require('scanr')('YOUR_TOKEN')
scanr.ocr('/path/to/image.png', function(err, text){
  console.log(text);
}
</code></pre>
          <h5>response</h5>
          <code>{text: 'Hello world!'}</code></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="mdl-tabs__panel" id="ruby">
          <h5>request</h5>
<pre><code>gem install scanr
scanr = Scanr.new 'YOUR_TOKEN'
p scanr.ocr '/path/to/image.png'
</code></pre>
          <h5>response</h5>
          <code>{text: 'Hello world!'}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

